    <item>
      <title>Key Haul at the Waterfall - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/19/key-haul/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/19/key-haul/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 Oct 2024 03:59:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13049" class="post-13049 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Key Haul at the Waterfall&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;As soon I started up the game this evening, I saw a huge dragonfly fly by. I was thinking it was a banded dragonfly, so I got my net out and chased it down. I lost it momentarily, but I ran into it again near the windmill. I swung my net and caught it! It was actually a giant petaltail, though.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8039-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="I caught a giant petaltail! I tamed the beast!" class="wp-image-13050" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I had forgotten all about these, since they&amp;#8217;re not in New Horizons at all (and pretty rare in the other games too).&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I visited Jeremiah, he was repeating a phrase: &amp;#8220;I&amp;#8217;ll catch one!&amp;#8221; He was hoping to catch a long locust today. It probably won&amp;#8217;t happen as long as he&amp;#8217;s staying in his house, though. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8040-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Jeremiah: I'll catch one!" class="wp-image-13051" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;A bug, or a cold? 😉&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After making my rounds, I took a break and then returned later (after 8 p.m.). At the Roost, I asked for a random song, and K.K. performed K.K. Dixie for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8041-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Dixie." class="wp-image-13052" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Antonio locked himself out of his house, and he was feeling &lt;em&gt;antsy&lt;/em&gt;. So I went sniffing around the river for his key. It took a little while, but I eventually fished it out near the waterfall.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8042-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="I caught a key! ...Whose key is this?" class="wp-image-13053" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It then took me almost as long to find Antonio wandering around. 😛 But he was relieved to have his key, and he rewarded me with a tall sputnoid.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8044-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Antonio: Ooh! That shape! It's back! No mistake! My key!" class="wp-image-13054" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Patty pinged me, and she surprised me by telling me she was &lt;em&gt;moo-ving&lt;/em&gt; out of town!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8043-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Patty: I'm moving, how-now!" class="wp-image-13055" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I thought about it for a second, and I decided to let her go. True, she&amp;#8217;s only been here for two months, but she isn&amp;#8217;t exactly one of my favorites. It&amp;#8217;s better to have her go, than to risk one of my favorites moving out without warning.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I posted my latest ACCF video, City Folk Moments #21. Here it is:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="ACCF - City Folk Moments #21 (Animal Crossing)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/GZGW94M8x9E?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;See you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/19/key-haul/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-19T23:59:00-04:00"&gt;October 19, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-20T00:20:19-04:00"&gt;October 20, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8039-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Merengue&amp;#039;s Photo - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/19/merengues-photo/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/19/merengues-photo/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 Oct 2024 01:20:48 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8400" class="post-8400 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Merengue&amp;#8217;s Photo&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, I caught a scallop while diving, and Pascal popped up to ask for it. He started talking about coconuts, of all things. It was weird.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pascal-coconuts-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Pascal: Hard shell, milk on the inside, kinda hairy... Coconuts have a lot going on, maaan." class="wp-image-8404" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I wasn&amp;#8217;t sure where he was going with that at first.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In exchange for the scallop, he gave me some mermaid shoes. That was different; he almost always just gives me pearls.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, I found three of my cutest villagers (Ketchup, Bob, and June) all singing (and swaying from side to side) in unison outside of Resident Services! It was so cute!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/3sing2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Ketchup, Bob, and June singing in unison at the plaza." class="wp-image-8405" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I went afk after coming out of Able Sisters. Moments later, a balloon present flew by, completely blocking me from sight on-screen.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/able-balloon-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="A balloon present flies by, in front of Able Sisters." class="wp-image-8408" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I returned to shoot the balloon down, and it had 5,000 bells inside. 💰&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over at my D.I.Y. workbench, I crafted a hyacinth lamp. I wrapped it up and gave it to Merengue. She loved it, and she gave me her photo in return!! What a sweet deal!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/merengue-give-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Merengue: As a thank-you, please take my Merengue's photo." class="wp-image-8409" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Thank you, Merengue!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I now have photos of all ten of my current villagers. 😁 I took her photo home and put it in my photo display room. Her favorite quote on the back is &amp;#8220;Life is a piece of cake.&amp;#8221; 🍰&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/merengue-photo-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Merengue's photo on display in my villager photo gallery." class="wp-image-8410" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes from this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Sunday night, K.K. performed K.K. D&amp;amp;B for me, Static, and Ketchup.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped out Gullivarrr on Monday, and he sent me a pirate-treasure crown the next day.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tonight, K.K. performed K.K. Chorinho for me, Bones, Agent S, and Louie.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Enjoy the rest of your weekend! See you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/19/merengues-photo/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2024-10-19T21:20:48-04:00"&gt;October 19, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pascal-coconuts-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Way of the Owl - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/17/way-of-the-owl/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/17/way-of-the-owl/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Oct 2024 23:42:23 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7732" class="post-7732 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;The Way of the Owl&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Octavian was still sick yesterday, so I gave him some more medicine. But by today, he was feeling better. He thanked me by giving me a parquet floor.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/octavian-thanks-150x112.jpg" alt="Octavian: Thanks for watchin' my back when I was down." class="wp-image-7736" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Last week, I mentioned that Whitney&amp;#8217;s house looks really nice. I&amp;#8217;m not the only one who thinks so, because she told me that the Happy Room Academy gave her 5,071 points. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/whitney-5k-150x112.jpg" alt="Whitney: The result? 5,071 points! Not bad, huh? In fact, it's pretty great!" class="wp-image-7733" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That might not sound high compared to player houses (which are bigger and have multiple rooms), but that&amp;#8217;s really high for a villager! Usually when they say their house score, it&amp;#8217;s a 3-digit score.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I visited Drift today, he asked if I thought his house was nice. The two options were &amp;#8220;Yeah!&amp;#8221; and &amp;#8220;I&amp;#8217;ve seen better.&amp;#8221; Since I saw the same dialogue recently and answered &amp;#8220;yeah,&amp;#8221; I decided to pick the other option today, just to see how he reacted. And he didn&amp;#8217;t disappoint. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/drift-wreck-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: Whoa, champ! Better check yourself before I wreck you, rrrrribbit!" class="wp-image-7734" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Don&amp;#8217;t wreck me, frog boy. I&amp;#8217;m just messing with you. 😆&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found a note in a bottle on the beach, and it was a bit of a downer.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/note-farewell2024-150x112.jpg" alt="Listen up! If you're reading this, it's probably too late for me! Take care of things for me, would you? Farewell." class="wp-image-7740" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Saharah was in town, and she asked me to make some deliveries for her. The first one was a carpet for Blathers, who I had to wake up. Being sleepy in daytime is &amp;#8220;the way of the owl,&amp;#8221; he said. 🦉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/blathers-wayofowl-150x112.jpg" alt="Blathers: I can't help but be sleepy during the day, I'm afraid. 'Tis the way of the owl!" class="wp-image-7735" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Next, I took a carpet for Phyllis over to town hall (and gave it to Pelly). Saharah then rewarded me with a shoji screen.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/saharah-shojilunar-150x112.jpg" alt="Saharah: Do you want a shoji screen or a lunar surface?" class="wp-image-7737" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I visited Caroline, she told me she would like some pink furniture. As I was walking out her door, I realized that I actually &lt;em&gt;had &lt;/em&gt;a piece of pink lovely furniture in my pockets already! So I went right back in and gave her the lovely dresser.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/caroline-how-150x112.jpg" alt="Caroline: How in the world did you know I was into collecting pink furniture?" class="wp-image-7738" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;You literally just asked me for it.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She rewarded me with a round carpet. I left and re-entered her house again, just to see if she put the dresser on display; she did.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/clean-up-150x112.jpg" alt="Me, looking into Caroline's dresser: Wow! Is it THAT hard to clean up a little before having guests over?" class="wp-image-7739" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;How could it be that messy already???&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Have a great day (or night), and I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Update: I just wanted to add that I&amp;#8217;m now on Bluesky! &lt;a href="https://bsky.app/profile/jvgsjeff.bsky.social"&gt;Follow me there&lt;/a&gt; if you&amp;#8217;d like!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt; &lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/17/way-of-the-owl/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-17T19:42:23-04:00"&gt;October 17, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-17T22:26:05-04:00"&gt;October 17, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/octavian-thanks.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Midge and Chip? - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/12/midge-and-chip/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/12/midge-and-chip/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Oct 2024 03:55:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13040" class="post-13040 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Midge and Chip?&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;I missed today&amp;#8217;s fishing tournament (though I did participate in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/"&gt;New Horizons&lt;/a&gt;), but Chip informed me of the results: Midge was the big winner with her 46-inch sea bass. Congrats, Midge!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Antonio asked me to make a delivery for him, and I was happy to help. I trotted the gift over to Roscoe; it was a Dutch shirt.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/accf-roscoe-fit-sm-150x84.jpg" alt="Roscoe: Well, let's see how she fits, giddyup!" class="wp-image-13041" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Roscoe was happy with it, and he looked very pretty in his new dress! 😆 &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8036-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Roscoe wearing his new dress." class="wp-image-13042" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I returned to Antonio, he rewarded me with a new hearth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Midge was talking about how she was so impressed by Chip&amp;#8217;s appetite, especially the way he gobbles down every fish you give him without hesitation. She even started imagining being &lt;em&gt;married &lt;/em&gt;to him!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8037-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Midge: Could you imagine being married to Chip? You'd spend all your time in the kitchen, frying up fish!" class="wp-image-13043" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But then she clarified that &lt;em&gt;she &lt;/em&gt;didn&amp;#8217;t want to marry him. It was a weird bit of dialogue, though.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/accf-midge-chip-sm-150x84.jpg" alt="Midge: ...Oh, no, wait, I'm not saying I want to marry Chip or anything like that, I eat bugs!" class="wp-image-13044" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I sold a little fruit while I waited for 8:00 for K.K. Slider to appear, and then I headed to the Roost. I asked the traveling musician for a random song, and he performed Agent K.K. for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8038-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: Agent K.K.." class="wp-image-13045" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Shortly after that, I wrapped up my game for the night. Did any of you attend K.K.&amp;#8217;s show tonight, or am I the only one who still does? 😆 Leave a comment below, and I&amp;#8217;ll see you all next time.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/12/midge-and-chip/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-12T23:55:00-04:00"&gt;October 12, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-13T00:59:43-04:00"&gt;October 13, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/accf-roscoe-fit-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>100 Million Bells - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 12 Oct 2024 23:09:31 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8384" class="post-8384 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;100 Million Bells&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday (the day after being &amp;#8220;purified&amp;#8221;), Katrina sent me a lucky gold turtle figurine. So I &lt;em&gt;did &lt;/em&gt;get an item from her after all! This is what it looks like:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/gold-turtle-figurine-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="The gold turtle figurine from Katrina." class="wp-image-8387" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Anicotti the ugly Muppet mouse was camping at my campsite. I had zero interest in letting her move in. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/anicotti-camper-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Anicotti, at the campsite: Hi there! I'm Anicotti! I'm here on a camping trip! You live on this island? Tres cool." class="wp-image-8388" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;There was a heavy meteor shower last night, and I wished on a bunch of shooting stars.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/wish2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Wishing on a shooting star." class="wp-image-8389" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As a result, I found 17 star fragments and three Libra fragments on the beach today.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The fall fishing tournament was underway this afternoon, so I gave it a go. On my first attempt, I caught six fish in the three-minute limit, which was good for eight points.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/tourney-6-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Reel it in! The Fishing Tourney is over!" class="wp-image-8390" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;C.J. paid me 2,250 bells for those six fish, and I decided to play again. But my second attempt was even worse: I only caught four fish, although I caught a 5th one at the buzzer that didn&amp;#8217;t count. He paid me 5,580 for those fish. I then redeemed ten points for a reward, a fish doorplate.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Since he was in town though, I decided to get a bunch of fish out of storage for him. It included the last of my summer shark hauls. I sold the 32 fish to C.J. for 524,400 bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="620" height="247" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/32fish-sm-250x100.jpg" alt="The 32 fish I sold to C.J." class="wp-image-8386" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That was a nice chunk of change, and I immediately went into town hall to deposit my money. Thanks to this influx of fishy bells, I was able to bump my savings balance up to 100 million bells for the first time!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/100m-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Savings Balance: 100,000,000 bells." class="wp-image-8391" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;This is the 2nd Animal Crossing game in which I&amp;#8217;ve reached this milestone, with New Leaf being the other. Of course, bells were considerably harder to earn in the older games.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There isn&amp;#8217;t a K.K. Slider concert tonight due to the tournament. But here are a few other quick notes about this past week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;I helped Gulliver on Tuesday, and he sent me another sombrero.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Flick was in town on Wednesday, and he paid me 97k for 19 bugs.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I returned a lost item to Bob yesterday, and he rewarded me with a delivery jacket.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I shot down a balloon present and found 30,000 bells inside. 💰&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Today, I caught three banded dragonflies! I actually saw one other one too, but it got away.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-12T19:09:31-04:00"&gt;October 12, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-12T19:15:44-04:00"&gt;October 12, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/gold-turtle-figurine-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Acorn Festival 2024 - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/10/acorn-festival-2024/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/10/acorn-festival-2024/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 10 Oct 2024 23:02:09 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7718" class="post-7718 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Acorn Festival 2024&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;The Acorn Festival is underway, and Cornimer was standing outside of town hall for the event. He started things off by giving me my fortune.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/acorn-fortune2024-150x112.jpg" alt="Your secret fortune: Mini Acorn. Life: 50-50 chance. Hopes: Make a decision. Karma: Do ten chin-ups. Look behind you!" class="wp-image-7719" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I have a 50-50 chance at life? I&amp;#8217;m not sure what that means, but I seem to be alive at the moment, so I guess I&amp;#8217;m doing okay? 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I gave him my first six acorns, and he gave me a mush stool.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/cornimer-watching-150x112.jpg" alt="Cornimer: And remember, li'l oakie... The great and mighty Cornimer is always watching!" class="wp-image-7720" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I went around town, picking up acorns as I went. Filbert told me that it was raining acorns! That&amp;#8217;s not exactly true, but I knew what he meant. Kinda. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/filbert-acorns-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert: It's raining acorns! They're just falling from the sky!" class="wp-image-7721" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Many of my villagers were talking about Cornimer, and in some cases, they were even singing songs about him.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/bones-cornimer-150x112.jpg" alt="Bones: Take off your hat! And look around! 'Cause Cornimer has come to town!" class="wp-image-7722" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And Truffles? Well, she was being her usual rude self.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/truffles-jealous-150x112.jpg" alt="Truffles: I'm doing SOOOOO good!! ...WHAT?! You don't CARE how I'm doing?! JEALOUS MUCH?!" class="wp-image-7723" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At &lt;s&gt;GameStop&lt;/s&gt; Nookington&amp;#8217;s, I traded in some &lt;s&gt;used video games&lt;/s&gt; rotten acorns for some big money. 😉 &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/nook-8bells-150x112.jpg" alt="Tom Nook: Let's see, all together, I'll pay 8 bells for everything!" class="wp-image-7724" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;You can&amp;#8217;t give rotten acorns to Tortimer, so I filled up the recycle bin with them, and just sold the rest for 2 bells apiece.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I got to see the inside of Whitney&amp;#8217;s house now that she is all unpacked, and it looks nice!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/whitney-house-150x112.jpg" alt="The inside of Whitney's house in Animal Crossing: Wild World (ACWW)." class="wp-image-7725" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Octavian was still sick with a cold, so I gave him another dose of medicine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;By the time I finished cleaning up all the acorns, I had given Tortimer 109 acorns in total. He gave me seven pieces of furniture in return: a mush lamp, stool, chair, stand, end table, dresser, and closet.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/cornimer-109-150x112.jpg" alt="Cornimer: The number of acorns you've given me is 109!" class="wp-image-7726" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I checked my storage to see if I had any leftover acorns there, but I didn&amp;#8217;t. So I sold my seven mush items at the store, and Tom Nook paid 15,600 bells for them all.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Acorn Festival continues through Sunday, so you still have time to check it out for yourself! Good luck out there!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt; &lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/10/acorn-festival-2024/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-10T19:02:09-04:00"&gt;October 10, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-10T19:04:37-04:00"&gt;October 10, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/acorn-fortune2024.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
